{
  "text": "The process of metastasis involves sequential steps of tumor cell detachment from the primary tumor, adherence to and proteolysis of endothelial basement membranes, intravasation into the circulation, and initiation of secondary tumors in distal organs. Most of the tumor cells that enter the circulation die, and only a very small proportion succeed in establishing metastases [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The aims of this study were to detect the presence of circulating tumor cells perioperatively and to determine the relationship of tumor cells in blood to disease-free survival following curative resection for colorectal cancer.",
